rt because St Thomas's doubts have made him seem a very human character."],"variants":[]}],"historicEvents":[{"id":1705197,"age":36,"year":"1455","julianDay":2252488,"title":"Wars of the Roses","description":"Wars of the Roses was a series of English civil wars for control of the throne of England between the royal families House of Lancaster and the House of York. The name of the war was derived as the red rose was the symbol of the Lancastrians and the white rose was the symbol of the Yorks.","url":"https://www.history.com/topics/british-history/wars-of-the-roses","urlTitle":"History - Wars of the Roses","jurisdictionLevel":2}],"lifeSummary":"When Thomas Englefield was born in 1419, in Englefield, Berkshire, England, his father, Philip Englefield, was 44 and his mother, Alice Rossell, was 40. He married Mary Margaret Clifton in 1431, in Englefield, Berkshire, England, United Kingdom. They were the parents of at least 1 daughter. He died on 26 February 1464, in Englefield, Berkshire, England, United Kingdom, at the age of 45."},"et":{"1419–26 February 1464":"1419–26. veebruar 1464","1405–1470":"1405–1470","1419–1464":"1419–1464","1421–1473":"1421–1473","1425–1470":"1425–1470","1419–1456":"1419–1456","1438–1501":"1438–1501","1376–1429":"1376–1429","1380–1429":"1380–1429","1473":"1473","1470":"1470","Abt 1429":"umbes 1429","1380":"1380","Aft 1429":"pärast 1429","       1456":"1456","1425":"1425","1501":"1501","1456":"1456","about 1404":"umbes 1404","1455":"1455","about 1438":"umbes 1438","1421":"1421","1431":"1431","1376":"1376","1464":"1464","1419":"1419","1429":"1429","26 February 1464":"26. veebruar 1464","1438":"1438","1405":"1405","Calne, Wiltshire, England, United Kingdom":"Calne, Wiltshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom","Englefield, Berkshire, England":"Englefield, Berkshire, Inglismaa, United Kingdom"},"fi":{"1419–26 February 1464":"1419–26. helmikuuta 1464","1405–1470":"1405–1470","1419–1464":"1419–1464","1421–1473":"1421–1473","1425–1470":"1425–1470","1419–145